content.description:
A fun diversion! Start on side-pulls in a crack low and move left on the slab, then back right into the crack system. 

  The plates mid-route are SOLID. Make a great lie-back move then cross over to a sweet pocket under a bulging roof and to a sloper match under the roof. Workup the crack on the right.
content.protection: TR, sandstone too questionable for gear. Set the TR to the left of the tree lowest down from the top. I will post a pic.
content.location: Center of wall, follows right angling crack in the center of the wall then heads to the right crack higher up for better rock. (Straight up is choss).

content.description: Shady area west of Group Camp B. Below "Press It Out".
